abstract: Pennsylvania Atty Gen Kathleen Kane says she is planning on seeking re-election and hopes suspension of her law license will be lifted before April primary to ensure her eligibility for office; license was suspended due to criminal allegations, including felony perjury, against her.
lead_paragraph: Ms. Kane said Thursday she did not think she would be eligible to run for a second term next year if her law license remained suspended.

headline.main: Pennsylvania: State Attorney General Kathleen Kane Uncertain of Running Again
headline.print_headline: Pennsylvania: Top Lawyer Uncertain of Running Again
